Modified ArcSDM tools

Spatial Data Modeler 5 for ArcGis pro, Version ArcSdm 5.03 for ArcGis (Pro and Desktop)
Updated 7.10.2020
  
Changed tools and other files
-----------------------------
Standard toolbox of ArcSDM 5 works on ArcGis Desktop 10.3-10.7.1, however Experimental toolbox requires components that cannot be installed on ArcGis desktop and doesn't work. ArcGis pro is supported from version 2.5+ forward.
These changes have been made in part in collaboration with the University of Unicamp, Brazil.

Toolbox
-------
Toolbox\ArcSDM.pyt modifications:
9.6.2020: Grand Wofe start method is modified on 
7.10.2020: Calculate Weights:
- if the workspace is File Geodatabase (GDB database), the menu code deletes the numbers from the beginning of the Weights Table name and the underscore if there are any at the beginning of the Input Raster name. The name of the Weights Table is formed from the beginning of the name of the Input Raster. In this case, the Weights Table is written as a File Geodatabase table and its name must start with a letter and not a number.
- if the workspace is a File System folder, the menu code appends the .dbf type extension after the Weights Table name, because in this case the Weights Table is a dBase database table and is written to the workspace folder. In this case, the Weights Table name may also start with numbers, so they will not be deleted.
7.10.2020: Logistic Regression: The parameter field Evidence type has been changed to a plain text field in which as many letters (a, c, d, or o) must be entered as there are Input Rasters and the letters must be separated by semicolons; as this is consistent with the Grand Wofe tool.

