logisticregression.py 7.10.2020
1. os.path.basename (Input_Raster[:9]) has been changed to os.path.basename (Input_Raster)[:9].
The previous format picked the first 9 characters from the beginning of the folder path of the Input raster. If the Input raster folder path started with a disk ID and a root folder (eg C: \ Users) with a root folder name shorter than 6 characters, that substring pick returned an empty string that caused the error ERROR 999999: Error executing function. The table name is invalid. Failed to execute (Lookup).
The new format returns the first 9 characters from the beginning of the name part of the Input raster and thus from the beginning of the folder path and the same problem no longer exists. The name does not have to be 9 characters long.
2. gp.Lookup_sa (Temp_Raster, "GEN_CLASS", Output_Raster) has been changed to Output_Raster = gp.Lookup_sa (Temp_Raster, "GEN_CLASS") because the previous format has expired and did not work after the change in section 1.
3. The Fortran application sdmlr.exe will not work if the workspace is File System and the length of the Scratch Workspace name exceeds 51 characters. The source code for Fortran is no longer available, but as a former Fortran coder, I think this is too little space for the name of the scratch Workspace to which \ scratch \ logpol.tba is added. In Fortran, a space of a certain size must be reserved for each string, eg CHARACTER * 30 NAME, and strings in excess of that are truncated, leaving the folder reference incomplete. In this case, the error was (path) logpol.tba does not exist. Error in case.dat or param.dat. The Workspace folder name can be longer, but the scratch Workspace folder name cannot be longer than 51 characters.
4. Text entered in a field called Evidential Theme in the LRcoeff raster is truncated if the length of the text exceeds the maximum length of the field by 256 characters. An error occurred ERROR 999999: Error executing function. The row contains a bad value. [LR_coeff]. The row contains a bad value. [Theme]. in Execute vTabLR2rows.InsertRow (vTabLR2row)
5. If the workspace is File Geodatabase, the tool code removes numbers and underscores from the beginning of the raster names to be written to the database, if there are any at the beginning of the Input Raster name.

